org.rsna.ctp.objects

Class XmlObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rsna.ctp.objects.FileObject
      • org.rsna.ctp.objects.XmlObject

  • public class XmlObject
extends FileObject
    A generic XML object for clinical trials metadata, providing parsing and access to certain common elements.

      • getUID

        public java.lang.String getUID()
        Get the UID of this object. This method looks in several places it:
        1. the uid attribute of the root element
        2. the uniqueIdentifier attribute of the root element (for AIM compatibility)
        3. the uid child element of the root element
        4. the uid attribute of the first child element of the root element
        If the UID is missing, a UID is generated from the hash of the text of the XML.
        Overrides:
        getUID in class FileObject
        Returns:
        the UID.

      • getStudyDate

        public java.lang.String getStudyDate()
        Convenience method to get the contents of the best study date which is available for the file. This method looks in several places:
        1. the date attribute of the root element
        2. the study-date attribute of the root element
        If no date is available it returns the empty string.
        Overrides:
        getStudyDate in class FileObject
        Returns:
        the empty string.

      • getDescription

        public java.lang.String getDescription()
        Get the description for this object. This method looks in two places to find the description element:
        1. the description child element of the root element
        2. the description child of the first child of the root element.
        Overrides:
        getDescription in class FileObject
        Returns:
        the description, or the file name if it cannot be obtained.

      • getValue

        public java.lang.String getValue(java.lang.String path)
        Get the value of the node identified by a path. This method is a convenience method that can only be relied on if the path to the node can be found by taking the first element matching each step of the path.
        Parameters:
        path - the path from the root element to the node. Note that this method uses the XmlUtil.getValueViaPath(String) method, and the path syntax is slightly different from that of XPath. Specifically, attributes are identified as "node@attribute" rather than "node/@attribute".
        Returns:
        the value, or the empty string if the node identified by the path is missing.
